sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Tuesday said its second quarter profit rose 6.8% from last year, beating analyst expectations and sending its shares higher in premarket trading.
The Atlanta-based company reported second quarter net income of $1.19 billion, or 72 cents per share, compared with $1.12 billion, or 66 cents per share, in the year-ago period.
Net sales rose 1.8% from last year, to $19.41 billion.
On average, Wall Street analysts expected a slightly smaller profit of 71 cents per share, albeit on slightly higher sales of $19.6 billion.
Looking ahead the company raised its full-year profit forecast to $1.90 per share from a prior outlook of $1.88.
It cut its full-year sales forecast, however, saying it now expects a sales gain of 2.6% for the year.
It had previously forecast a 3.5% gain.
We had removed shares of HD from our recommended list back on May 25, when the stock was trading at $33.22.
The company has a 3.43% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $27.38.
The stock has technical support in the $25 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $32 price levels.
We would remain on the sidelines for now.
